&lt;p&gt;If you would like to work for a forward thinking organisation who puts patients first, has safety and quality at the heart of everything they do, invests and develops their workforce, encourages innovation and supports positive change then you’re ready to join us at East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Calling all Trainee Nursing Associates who qualify at East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust June 2020, or external Trainee Nursing Associates about to qualify in 2020, or current Registered Nursing Associates. We are looking for enthusiastic, motivated, and creative individuals who can be a role model to junior staff and demonstrate the Trust’s values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering you the opportunity to join our nursing team as a Band 4 Nursing Associate on our 20 bedded Diabetes and Endocrinology ward D1. You will be given a structured orientation program and preceptorship to further develop your skills, confidence and competencies in patient care. We look forward to meeting you and supporting you in your new role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Please note this post is for a qualified position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFrancesco CostanzoTelephone number01254 733810&lt;/p&gt;
